cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision and graphics, specifically with inferring a 3D representation of a scene from a single image. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves learning and optimization, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of a differentiable novel view renderer suggests that the paper could also be relevant to cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper's focus on inferring a 3D representation of a scene could be relevant to robotics, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics).
